                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;First issue isn&apos;t a reason it&apos;s bad, only a difference in semantics.  Second issue seems to me a reason (on top of clashes between libraries doing the same) that altering the prototype of a built-in datatype is bad, rather than that for..in is bad.&lt;/span&gt;

