            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@Stewart: &lt;b&gt;All objects&lt;/b&gt; in JS are associative.  A JS Array is an object, so yes, its associative too, but thats not what its for.  If you want to iterate over an object&apos;s &lt;i&gt;keys&lt;/i&gt;, use &lt;code&gt;for (var key in object)&lt;/code&gt;.  If you want to iterate over an arrays &lt;i&gt;elements&lt;/i&gt;, however, use &lt;code&gt;for(var i = 0; i &amp;lt; array.length; i += 1)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
